-- Italy's Big Banks Need $24 Billion to Meet Basel 3 Rules, Prometeia Says
-- B y   J e r r o l d   C o l t e n   a n d   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 2010-11-04T12:22:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/italy-s-big-banks-need-24-billion-to-meet-basel-3-rules-prometeia-says.html
Italy’s five biggest banks will need
17 billion euros in capital to reach a 7 percent common-equity
target under so-called Basel 3 rules, research institute
Prometeia said in a report released today.  The lenders’ growing profitability in the next few years
should allow them to fill their capital gap, Prometeia said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  